5:
A study hall? 
You mean here in Starview Village?
9:
If you've no objections, I would like to 
start one, yes.

17:
For the most part, though nothing 
quite so grand or structured.
19:
The study hall I ran in Yamato was a

If you already have one, then why 
open another here of all places?

Hmm...
Worlds are crossing, and Starview is 
their crossroad.
30:
We approach a new era—one where 
peoples and cultures will inevitably 
intersect.
32:
While great wonders await, so too do 
great perils. 
Confusion, conflicts... Just like when 
the two Yamatos merged.

I wish to offer inheritors of that future 
knowledge of worlds afar, in hopes they 
will choose diplomacy over the blade.
44:
Agreed. Let's set up a space in the 
library.

In the library? Are you sure, Stella?

61:
Thank you. I don't know how I can 
repay you.

Actually, if you wouldn't mind, there's

Hello, I'm Stella. I'm looking forward to 
teaching.

91:
What are you doing here, Hellcat?

Sides, I'm not the hellcat anymore.

102:

119:
Nadir. My name's Nadir. Better

time.
128:

141:
All right, is everyone ready to start 
class?
